5000|$|August Escoffier {{notes in}} Le Guide Culinaire that the {{commonly}} used [...] "English-style" [...] coating in these dishes is an economical {{substitute for the}} original treatment <b>with</b> chopped <b>truffles.</b> While chicken suprême and cervelle de veau are prepared this way, other dishes à la Maréchale in his guide, such as tournedos and foie gras collops, are treated <b>with</b> <b>truffles.</b> A garnish of truffles and green asparagus tips is nowadays common for dishes à la Maréchale.|$|R
